"In February 2012, at the Barcelona Mobile World Congress, the term Bring Your Own Device (BYOD) was coined. Unlike so many IT innovations that take time to filter into public consciousness, BYOD was suddenly everywhere – something that had crept up on us and, once given a name, was visible everywhere. Once employees are allowed to use their own phones, how long before they feel entitled to deploy their own software, hardware or SaaS services? There is no simple formula that can address this ‘shadow IT’ problem, explains Marc Meulensteen of Spirent Communications. What is needed is a carefully balanced combination of expert outsourced skills plus in-house experience and a thorough understanding of your own business."
